</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-BLAZERS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BLAZERS FEEL CONFIDENT WITHIN CONFINES OF HOME 
</HEADLINE>
   By TOM SPOUSTA   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   PORTLAND, Ore. _ The ultrasound wire poked from underneath the
bandage on his left hand, causing Scottie Pippen's two dislocated
fingers to look like an antenna.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's some new technology we're trying out, to see if Mike can
send me some signals from the bench,'' Pippen, referring to Coach
Mike Dunleavy, said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Indeed, Pippen was a beacon for the Portland Trail Blazers as
they avoided elimination with a 96-88 victory Tuesday night against
the Lakers at Los Angeles. Even after sustaining the injury to his
nonshooting hand early in the second quarter, Pippen continued to
play aggressively and energized the Trail Blazers' chances in the
four-of-seven-game Western Conference finals.
</P>
<P>
   For a team that trails three games to two, the Trail Blazers
sound as though they are in command of this series. Their
confidence hinged on the fact that Game 6 is Friday night at home
in the Rose Garden, where the Lakers won Games 3 and 4.
</P>
<P>
   The Trail Blazers contend that the odds of losing three straight
games at home are as improbable as Pippen's not playing Friday
night.
</P>
<P>
   The Trail Blazers had the fifth-best home record in the National
Basketball Association during the regular season and were 5-0 in
the playoffs until the Lakers beat them.
</P>
<P>
   ``Scottie gave up his body for the whole game and really
motivated us to take the ball to the hole strong,'' Brian Grant
said of Pippen's 22 points, 6 steals, 6 rebounds and 4 blocked
shots in Game 5. ``That is the thing we haven't been doing the past
couple games.''
</P>
<P>
   Pippen said of his two dislocated fingers: ``I feel better. I've
got a little more motion in them. I'll be fine.``
</P>
<P>
   Pippen's hand and the sprained foot of the Lakers' Kobe Bryant's
are the subplots to Game 6.
</P>
<P>
   While Pippen took control of his team, Bryant faded from the
Lakers' offense, especially after hurting his foot in the first
quarter. He forced shots and passes, finishing with 17 points on
4-of-13 shooting. And he had six turnovers before fouling out with
4 minutes 45 seconds to play. He missed practice on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The Trail Blazers' defense, especially Pippen, has clamped down
hard on Bryant, who is 9 of 28 in the last two games. For the
series, he has averaged 17 points, shot 40.6 percent and made 15
turnovers, well off his numbers (24 points, 7 turnovers and 55.6
percent shooting) in three regular-season games against the Trail
Blazers.
</P>
<P>
   ``There had been a lot of talk about Kobe guarding Pippen and
doing what he had done,'' Dunleavy said. `Basically, I said the
game plan was to go at Kobe more.''
</P>
<P>
   Bryant's only breakout came in Game 3, when he scored 25 points,
including 18 in the first half, to keep the Lakers afloat with a
93-91 victory.
</P>
<P>
   ``They're not giving him any space to operate out there,''
Lakers Coach Phil Jackson said. ``I think that he's trying to
figure out how to get himself free. As a consequence, once he takes
his second dribble, they're able to jump all over him.'' &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
