with the front bumper seemingly ready to burrow in at any minute.
</P>
<P>
   It remains an off-road beast _ better even than its earlier
incarnation.
</P>
<P>
   Part of that has to do with its new engine, the optional
4.7-liter, 235-horsepower plant that replaces the 5.2 and 5.9
liters of old. This new powerplant has 15 more horsepower than the
