in this package.
</P>
<P>
   The five-speed transmission did a too-quick, jerky upshift in
lower gears than I would like, but once rolling was smooth in
shifting through higher gears. Disc brakes, assisted by ABS, at all
four wheels brought it to swift, sure stops.
</P>
<P>
   Nice Touch:
</P>
<P>
   --The auxiliary audio control buttons tucked on the backside of
the steering wheel. Felt as if I was playing a video game as I
fooled with volume and stations.
</P>
<P>
   Annoyance:
</P>
<P>
   --The placing of the driver's seat memory buttons on the door
panel above the armrest. My elbow kept hitting them and changing my
seat position.
</P>
<P>
   Royal Ford's e-mail address is ford(at) globe.com.
</P>
