   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ONLINE-PORN-ART (Undated) _ At a time when venture capitalists
and business leaders are falling all over themselves trying to
figure out how to make money on the Web, entrepreneurs in the
online adult entertainment industry are floating in profits. By
Patti Hartigan. 1,800 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   ONBUSINESS-COLUMN (Undated) _ Imagine, hard as it is may be,
that the party is over. Imagine that we are entering a period where
the stock market goes into an extended funk, where every dip is not
followed by an immediate rebound (like Thursday's), where returns
are mediocre, rather than spectacular. By Steven Syre and Charles
Stein. 775 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS &LR;   &UR; (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-FLOOR (Boston) _ On Monday morning, segments of the
original Boston Celtics' parquet floor will be auctioned, many of
them bearing the signature of the player whose most legendary move
came on that particular panel of varnished wood. By David Arnold.
965 words.
</P>
<P>
   OUTDOORS-COLUMN (Undated) _ The fish are in: The spring mix
combines ground fish such as cod and tautog with market-sized
haddock, wolffish, plenty of mackerel, and striped bass in nearly
every area along the coast. By Tony Chamberlain.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
