   PARENTS OF BIRMINGHAM BOMB VICTIMS TELL STORY OF BLACK SURVIVAL
IN AMERICA. Columnist Vernon Jarrett speaks by phone with his
longtime friend, Mrs. Alpha Robertson, 81, the mother of Carole
Robertson, one of the four teen-age girls murdered when racists
