<P>
   DOW _ Stocks soar following a weaker-than-expected May jobs
report. News that fewer jobs were created than forecast and that
the unemployment rate rose to 4.1 percent has some economists
predicting the Federal Reserve will put its interest rate hikes on
hold, at least after the June 27-28 meeting. The Nasdaq is up 180
points and the Dow 150. U.S. unemployment, seasonally adjusted for
the past 12 months and monthly change in payroll jobs. (Walker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COX-RADIO _ ATLANTA _ Cox Radio to announce today that it has
purchased Kiss 104 and WCNN-AM for about $300 million. Makes Cox
the biggest player in the Atlanta market. (Longino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   COKE-DASANI _ ATLANTA _ After a year on the market Coke will be
spending about 15 million on national TV ads for Dasani, its
bottled water product. Coke's also developed a new 12 oz. plastic
bottle so it can be sold in vending machines. (Unger, Atlanta
Journa l-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   AIRLINES _Shares of Northwest Airlines surged Friday after a
Minneapolis TV station reported the carrier's in talks to be
acquired by American. Such a deal, following last week's United-US
Airways deal, could force Delta to rekindle its courtship of
Continental. The NW-AMR talks are unconfirmed however, and could be
aimed at influencing DOJ consideration of United-US Airways.
(Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL _The first sponsors of the giant baseball promotion
will be named today, and at least two 6-foot plastic balls,
decorated for the Yankees by a New York artists and for the Braves
by a local artist, will be displayed at the Yankees-Braves game
tonight. (Poole, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
