conversation of Southern suburbs _ lower taxes, welfare reform,
crackdowns on crime _ has been supplanted by a new agenda: managing
growth and transportation, bringing in high-tech jobs, and above
all improving public education. In a swath of states from the
Carolinas to Mississippi, Democratic governors have made these
issues their own, and Republicans are struggling to keep up. By
David Firestone.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
