<P>
   CIGNA-PULLOUT (Los Angeles) _ Cigna Corp., the nation's
sixth-largest health maintenance organization, will stop offering a
Medicare HMO plan to almost 18,000 customers in Southern California
on Jan. 1, a company spokesman said. The company cited low
government reimbursement rates and competitive pressures. By Chris
Sieroty. (Will move in the ``f'' financial and ``n'' California
