Haynes, 75, who has seen 50 years of change in jazz from the best
vantage point _ the back of the bandstand, the rhythm section. He
has played with practically everybody of major significance since
the 1940s _ from Louis Armstrong to Thelonious Monk to Charlie
Parker and worked with vocalists Sarah Vaughn, Billie Holliday and
Ella Fitzgerald. A lot of that history can be heard on his new disc
on Verve/Universal called simply, ``The Roy Haynes Trio.''
