<SLUG> BC-GIULIANI-FUNDS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GIULIANI EASES TRANSFER OF FUNDS TO LAZIO
</HEADLINE>
  c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Mayor Rudolph Giuliani has come up with a plan that
his aides say will make it easier for the contributors to his
now-defunct campaign for the U.S. Senate to give their money to the
new Republican candidate, Rep. Rick Lazio.
</P>
<P>
   Giuliani's campaign will send cashier's checks to the
contributors, along with a letter from the mayor urging them to
endorse the checks over to Lazio's campaign. A stamped envelope
addressed to Lazio's campaign headquarters will be included in the
mailing, to make things even easier.
</P>
<P>
   The contributions in question amount to just under $3 million.
Bruce Teitelbaum, who managed Giuliani's campaign, said that no
decision had been made about how Giuliani would dispose of another
$3 million or so, out of $20 million raised, that will remain in
the campaign fund.
</P>
<P>
   Dan McLagan, a spokesman for Lazio, said, ``They're doing
everything they can to help, and we're very appreciative.''
</P>
</TEXT>
