<HEADLINE>
REDSKINS NEXT FOR SANDERS? 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Deion Sanders, one of the more talented and high profile players
in NFL history, was released Friday by the Dallas Cowboys. But
don't feel too bad for the Pro Bowl cornerback and kick returner,
because he will quite likely find a home in Washington by next
week.
</P>
<P>
   There is a slim chance the Cowboys will try to rework a deal
with Sanders, or that Sanders could end up in Tampa Bay, but all
indications, several team and league officials said Friday, are
that Sanders will be with the Redskins by Monday or Tuesday. Dallas
released Sanders because of salary-cap reasons.
</P>
<P>
   ``Deion was a great player for us,'' Jerry Jones, the Cowboys'
owner, said. ``But because of salary-cap reasons, we can't afford
to keep him.''
</P>
<P>
   The Redskins might play Sanders at safety as much as cornerback,
and his kick-return skills would make their special teams
dangerous. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-02-00 2329EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
